# Firebase Functions Environment Configuration
# ================================================================
# These credentials are stored as Firebase Secrets (not env vars)
# Use: firebase functions:secrets:set SECRET_NAME
# ================================================================

# Google OAuth Credentials
# Get these from Google Cloud Console > APIs & Services > Credentials
GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=your-google-client-id.apps.googleusercontent.com
GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET=your-google-client-secret

# Microsoft OAuth Credentials
# Get these from Azure Portal > App registrations
MICROSOFT_CLIENT_ID=your-microsoft-client-id
MICROSOFT_CLIENT_SECRET=your-microsoft-client-secret

# ================================================================
# HMRC OAuth Credentials (REQUIRED for HMRC RTI Submissions)
# ================================================================
# Register at: https://developer.service.hmrc.gov.uk/developer/applications
#
# IMPORTANT: These MUST be stored as Firebase Secrets, not env vars:
#   firebase functions:secrets:set HMRC_CLIENT_ID
#   firebase functions:secrets:set HMRC_CLIENT_SECRET
#
# For data encryption key:
#   firebase functions:secrets:set HMRC_ENCRYPTION_KEY
#
# ================================================================
# APPLICATION NAMING CONVENTION (REQUIRED)
# ================================================================
# Application Name (should match your company name):
#   firebase functions:config:set hmrc.application_name="Your Company Name"
# Or set as environment variable: HMRC_APPLICATION_NAME="Your Company Name"
#
# Example: HMRC_APPLICATION_NAME="1Stop HR Platform"
# Example: HMRC_APPLICATION_NAME="ABC Payroll Solutions"
#
# This is used for compliance auditing and validation
# ================================================================
# When registering your application with HMRC Developer Hub:
# - Application name MUST match your company name
# - Example: If your company is "1Stop HR Platform", name the application "1Stop HR Platform"
# - Example: If your company is "ABC Payroll Solutions", name the application "ABC Payroll Solutions"
# - This is required for HMRC compliance and identification
#
# ================================================================
# Compliance Requirements:
# ================================================================
# - Only ONE production application per organization
#   * Do NOT create multiple applications for each customer
#   * Use OAuth tokens to isolate customer traffic instead
# - Application name must match your company name
# - Use OAuth tokens to isolate customer traffic (not separate applications)
# - Never expose credentials to client-side code
# - Use sandbox for testing: https://test-api.service.hmrc.gov.uk
# - Use production for live: https://api.service.hmrc.gov.uk
# ================================================================
